============================================================
SHELL AND COMMAND RULES
============================================================

Use Windows PowerShell only.

Before running commands, confirm current directory:

Get-Location

If current directory is outside:

C:\Users\lieml\Desktop\Big Personal Web App\kost48surabaya-v3\kost48_full_frontend_backend_upgrade_bundle\final_bundle

STOP and report.

If the terminal is cmd.exe, bash, Git Bash, WSL, or any non-PowerShell shell:
STOP and report:
"Shell is not PowerShell. Please switch terminal to PowerShell before continuing."

Do NOT adapt by using cmd syntax.
Do NOT use curl.
Do NOT use bash commands.

All API tests must use Invoke-RestMethod.

Protected endpoint format:

$token="PASTE_TOKEN_HERE"; Invoke-RestMethod -Method Get -Uri "http://localhost:3000/api/..." -Headers @{Authorization="Bearer $token"}

JSON POST/PATCH/PUT format:

$token="PASTE_TOKEN_HERE"; Invoke-RestMethod -Method Patch -Uri "http://localhost:3000/api/..." -Headers @{Authorization="Bearer $token"} -ContentType "application/json" -Body '{"field":"value"}'

Do not use placeholder URLs like ID_STAY.
If an ID is unknown, say:
"replace with a real numeric ID"
and give an example such as:
http://localhost:3000/api/stays/9/cancel

============================================================
WORK MODE RULES
============================================================

Use one mode only:
- PLAN: audit, explain, sequence, decide scope
- ACT: edit code, build, verify minimal result

Do not mix PLAN and ACT.

For ACT:
- Work on one vertical slice only.
- Do not open a broad scope.
- Do not rewrite the whole backend/frontend.
- Do not touch unrelated modules.
- Do not run long UAT unless the user explicitly asks for final UAT.
- Do not create test data unless the current task explicitly requires it.
- Do not mutate database for exploratory testing.
- Prefer code patch + build first.
- Mark manual/API tests as PENDING for final verification when appropriate.

Current preferred strategy:
- M1 to M4: code batch first, build minimal only.
- M5/final gate: bigger UAT/manual verification.
- Avoid wasting tokens on long repeated UAT after every small patch.

