============================================================
M1 OWNER PROTECTION RULES
============================================================

For M1 Owner Protection Backend:

Scope:
- Backend only.
- Do not touch frontend.
- Do not touch docs.
- Do not reset DB.
- Do not run long UAT.
- Build only unless user asks for final verification.

Goal:
Prevent any non-OWNER role from locking, weakening, deleting, deactivating, or taking over OWNER accounts.

Rules:
- Protect all users with role OWNER.
- Do not hardcode email.
- Do not protect only admin@kost48.com.
- Do not protect only liem.lui@gmail.com.

Non-OWNER actor means any actor whose role is not OWNER:
- ADMIN
- STAFF
- TENANT
- any other non-OWNER role

A non-OWNER actor must not be able to:
- change OWNER role
- deactivate OWNER
- reset/change OWNER password through admin/staff route
- delete OWNER if endpoint exists
- grant OWNER role to another user
- make changes that prevent OWNER from login

OWNER should still be able to:
- login
- manage non-owner users according to existing rules

Admin/Staff should still be able to:
- manage non-owner users according to existing existing rules

Preferred implementation:
- Service-layer validation.
- Controller remains thin.
- Actor comes from JWT context.
- Error message in Bahasa Indonesia.
- No schema change unless absolutely necessary.
- If schema change seems needed, STOP and report.

============================================================
FINAL REPORT FORMAT
============================================================

At the end of every ACT, report:

1. Summary
- COMPLETE / PARTIAL / BLOCKED
- Short explanation only

2. Files changed
- File path
- One sentence explanation

3. Build result
- Command used
- PASS / FAIL

4. Verification
- Minimal checks performed
- Manual/API tests pending, if any

5. Git status
- Paste git status --short
- Paste git diff --stat

6. Risks / next step
- Only real risks
- Next recommended ACT

Do not overclaim.
Do not say PASS if only build was done.
Do not say UAT PASS unless UAT was actually done.